addValue

public void addValue(IPSFieldValue content)
Adds a field value. If isMultiValue() returns true the value will be added to the list. If isMultiValue() returns false any previous value will be over ridden by the value content.

Parameters:
content - value that will be added. Must not be null. Must be IPSFieldValue type supported by this field at run time. This is determined by this fields corresponding PSItemFieldMeta.getBackendDataType().
PSItemFieldMeta.getBackendDataType() returns IPSFieldValue supported
PSItemFieldMeta.DATATYPE_BINARY
PSBinaryValue Binary data type only accepts binary field value.
PSItemFieldMeta.DATATYPE_DATE
PSDateValue Date data type accepts PSDateValue
PSItemFieldMeta.DATATYPE_NUMERIC Numeric data type accepts PSTextValue.
PSItemFieldMeta.DATATYPE_TEXT
Text data type Accepts PSTextValue and PSXmlValue
When the field is loaded with data on an open. The backend types will determine which IPSFieldValue will be used to hold the data.

createFieldValue

public IPSFieldValue createFieldValue(String stringValue)
Creates and returns the appropriate field value for this field based on the backend data type.

Parameters:
stringValue - - The String representation of the value to use. This method converts the stringValue to the default type for each IPSFieldValue as follows:
  • Remains as String for PSTextValue.
  • Remains as String for PSXmlValue.
  • Base64 decoded and converted to a byte[] for PSBinaryValue.
  • Converted to default Date and DateFormat (using default Locale).
Cannot be null.
Returns:
IPSFieldValue the correct IPSFieldValue to use with this field. Not null.

equals

public boolean equals(Object obj)
Description copied from interface: IPSCmsComponent
Indicates whether some other object is "equal to" this one. All implementing classes must override this method as the default behavior is incorrect for deep clones. If the implementation does not follow the contract documented for this method in Object, then it must clearly state how it deviates from that contract. The following algorithm should be used:
  1. Call the base class (unless Object) and if true is returned, continue.
  2. Compare all members of current class.
  3. If all members are equal, return true.

loadXmlData

public void loadXmlData(Element sourceNode)
                 throws com.percussion.design.objectstore.PSUnknownNodeTypeException
This method is called to populate an object from its XML representation. It assumes that the object may already have a complete data structure, therefore method only overlays the data onto the existing object. An element node may contain a hierarchical structure, including child objects. The element node can also be a child of another element node.

It is important to note that this implementation of the method creates IPSFieldValue objects based on the backend data type. If the value in the EL_RAW_DATA elemnt cannot be parsed into a date and therefore the PSDateValue cannot be constructed a PSTextValue will be constructed in its place.

Specified by:
loadXmlData in class PSItemComponent
Parameters:
sourceNode - the XML element node from which to populate. Must not be null.
Throws:
com.percussion.design.objectstore.PSUnknownNodeTypeException - if the XML element node does not represent a type supported by this class.
